The paper discusses a logic-based framework for checking completeness guarantees of ontology reasoners, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the practical implications of incomplete reasoners in ontology-based information systems, which is relevant to database systems (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability requirements of ontology-based information systems, which is related to cybernetics (cs.CY).
